						               													<description>Pas de Charge is a set of rules for Napoleonic Miniatures. It is designed with the idea of recreating divisional and corps level battles during the period 1800 to 1815. It utilizes a figure scale of 1 model equaling 30 actual troops.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is based on the simultaneous movement concept. In order to achieve this, it is necessary to write orders. As a result, the sequence of play is as follows:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Phase 1- Order writing&amp;#10;Phase 2-Charges are announced&amp;#10;Phase 3-Counter charges are announced&amp;#10;Phase 4-Movement&amp;#10;Phase 5-Fire&amp;#10;Phase 6-Melee&amp;#10;Phase 7-Morale checks&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules contain a section on organization and mounting of figures for the main combatants of the era.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
